# MVP Priority Plan — *Lost-in-Woods*

The goal of the MVP is:

> Deliver a fully playable text-based survival game with working story progression, player choices, and save functionality.

Everything below is prioritized to ensure:

* Working demo
* Stable architecture
* Simple implementation
* Good grading presentation
* Easy future expansion

---

# 1. MVP PRIORITY LEVELS

| Priority | Description                                 |
| -------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| P1       | Critical — game cannot work without this    |
| P2       | Important — improves gameplay and usability |
| P3       | Optional — future enhancements              |

---

# 2. PRIORITIZED MVP REQUIREMENTS

# P1 — CORE REQUIREMENTS (MUST HAVE)

These features are mandatory for a playable MVP.

---

# 2.1 User Creation

## Purpose

Create a player profile before game starts.

## Requirements

* Input Name
* Input Age
* Select Gender
* Save player data

## Technical Notes

* Store player in database
* Auto-generate player ID

## Acceptance Criteria

* User can create profile successfully
* Validation works properly

---

# 2.2 Story Scene System

## Purpose

Display story content and choices.

## Requirements

* Show scene title
* Show scene description
* Show available choices
* Navigate to next scene

## Technical Notes

* Story data stored in database or JSON
* Scene loaded dynamically

## Acceptance Criteria

* User can move from one scene to another

---

# 2.3 Choice Outcome System

## Purpose

Allow user decisions to affect gameplay.

## Requirements

* Choices have outcomes
* Choices affect health
* Choices lead to different scenes

## Technical Notes

* Backend handles game logic
* Frontend only displays results

## Acceptance Criteria

* Different choices produce different outcomes

---

# 2.4 Health System

## Purpose

Add survival challenge.

## Requirements

* Player starts with 100 health
* Dangerous choices reduce health
* Healing choices restore health
* Health reaching 0 triggers Game Over

## Acceptance Criteria

* Health updates correctly after each choice

---

# 2.5 Game Over System

## Purpose

End failed gameplay properly.

## Requirements

* Detect health = 0
* Show Game Over screen
* Allow restart

## Acceptance Criteria

* User can restart after losing

---

# 2.6 Victory Ending

## Purpose

Complete the game.

## Requirements

* Final scene triggers victory
* Display ending message

## Acceptance Criteria

* User can finish story successfully

---

# 2.7 Save Progress

## Purpose

Prevent loss of gameplay progress.

## Requirements

* Save:

  * Current scene
  * Current health
  * Player data
* Resume latest progress

## Technical Notes

* Save automatically after each choice

## Acceptance Criteria

* Refreshing page restores progress

